short_description:
Looking for a slider, slash, fader that will display Website pages and not just jpegs or png files? Well you have found it. this simple raw HTML slider is designed to fit inside of a (approx.) 200 pixel by 1000 pixel iframe space and refreshes multiple--actually, infinite--pages of data... this means you can now slideshow all your info, not just pictures.

Instructions are as follows: 
1) unzip into a single isolated directory; 
2) create an iframe (<iframe src="http://subdomain.or-directory.com/index.html" height="246" width="1042" scrolling="no"></iframe>
) pointing to the first page, index.html; 
3) edit the fields in the pages with your favorite HTML/text editor. 

This particular 'slider' was made for a real estate site. You can liberalize at will by increasing the size of your iframe to accommodate the entire page and you now have built a Website-presentation app.
